    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`io.stdout:write()` gets truncated inside `vim.defer_fn()`. Not all strings get written.\n\nI found this issue while exploring <https://github.com/folke/snacks.nvim/issues/1785>.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nPut this in `init.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  for i = 1, 5, 1 do\n    io.stdout:write(string.rep(i, 4096))\n  end\nend, 100)\n```\n\nTo test this:\n\n    $ script nvim.log\n    $ /usr/bin/nvim --clean -u init.lua\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAsserts shouldn't fail here:\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nCHUNK_SIZE = 4096\n\nnvim_contents = Path('nvim.log').read_bytes()\n\nassert b'1' * CHUNK_SIZE in nvim_contents\nassert b'2' * CHUNK_SIZE in nvim_contents\nassert b'3' * CHUNK_SIZE in nvim_contents\nassert b'4' * CHUNK_SIZE in nvim_contents\nassert b'5' * CHUNK_SIZE in nvim_contents\n```\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot relevant\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty v1.1.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nSystem package manager",
